29/08/2006
SOCHI, Russia -- President Vladimir Putin met with Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic on Monday (28 August) to discuss bilateral relations. 
Russia was among the first countries to recognise Montenegro's independence and establish diplomatic relations. 
The two discussed economic issues, the Kosovo situation and relations between Serbia and Montenegro. 
(Pobjeda, Vijesti - 29/08/06; Interfax, Tanjug - 28/08/06)
